WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:14.257 --> 00:00:16.158
Find out that man's name.

3
00:00:21.266 --> 00:00:24.702
I have come to visit Robin of Locksley.
but find him not at home.

4
00:00:25.770 --> 00:00:29.104
Perhaps one of you would like to inform
me of his whereabouts.

5
00:00:29.174 --> 00:00:32.338
He and I need to have a little chat.
a conversation.

6
00:00:33.611 --> 00:00:34.977
Nobody knows.

7
00:00:35.781 --> 00:00:38.273
Nobody knows.

8
00:00:38.351 --> 00:00:41.046
Then... there is a reward.

9
00:00:41.119 --> 00:00:43.588
Shall we say... 20 pounds?

10
00:00:45.526 --> 00:00:48.585
And then all of a sudden somebody does know.

11
00:00:48.661 --> 00:00:51.096
Loosen your tongues or lose your tongues!

12
00:01:02.042 --> 00:01:03.670
Cut out his tongue...

13
00:01:03.745 --> 00:01:06.873
One an hour until somebody talks.

14
00:02:01.407 --> 00:02:04.104
- You're making a mistake.
- What?

15
00:02:04.178 --> 00:02:07.044
You're gonna send an army to hunt us down.
tear us limb from limb?

16
00:02:07.113 --> 00:02:09.513
You think we're frightened of the Sheriff?
Are we?

17
00:02:09.582 --> 00:02:12.950
- No.
- No. we are also against the Sheriff.

18
00:02:13.020 --> 00:02:16.616
- What do you want. a medal?
- We should be on the same side.

19
00:02:16.691 --> 00:02:18.317
Master. tell him.

20
00:02:22.230 --> 00:02:24.562
That rabbit is not...

21
00:02:24.633 --> 00:02:27.228
I think you'll find that rabbit
is not yet cooked.

22
00:02:27.303 --> 00:02:29.897
- I think you'll find he eats them raw.
- Raw?!

23
00:02:31.439 --> 00:02:34.604
- Is that wise? I mean. that is dangerous.
- Oh!

24
00:02:34.678 --> 00:02:36.702
Will you just shut up?

25
00:02:36.779 --> 00:02:38.475
- You're a noble?
- Yes...

26
00:02:41.117 --> 00:02:43.348
...and no.

27
00:02:43.419 --> 00:02:45.446
Smells like one.

28
00:02:45.523 --> 00:02:47.422
Smells lovely.

29
00:02:48.193 --> 00:02:49.625
Flowers. Lavender.

30
00:02:49.693 --> 00:02:51.685
- Rose petals.
- What?

31
00:02:51.763 --> 00:02:55.722
You rub it on. did you. lavender balm?
Yeah. you smell too.

32
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:58.861
No. I had a bath.
He washed in rose petals.

33
00:02:58.938 --> 00:03:04.342
And they reckon they're same side as us.
You know any outlaws who take lavender baths?

34
00:03:04.410 --> 00:03:06.242
No! John?

35
00:03:06.313 --> 00:03:07.938
It's not lavender.

36
00:03:09.515 --> 00:03:11.107
All right.

37
00:03:13.285 --> 00:03:14.685
Got a ha'penny here. John!

38
00:03:15.589 --> 00:03:18.285
You have the horses. leave him his ha'penny.

39
00:03:18.358 --> 00:03:20.087
How come you got no purse?

40
00:03:20.160 --> 00:03:22.628
Because I was not planning on
coming to the woods.

41
00:03:22.696 --> 00:03:24.392
- Is this what you do?
- What?

42
00:03:24.465 --> 00:03:27.263
- Stealing willy-nilly.
- Stealing willy-nilly?

43
00:03:27.335 --> 00:03:29.667
I can't understand what he's saying. Can you?

44
00:03:29.737 --> 00:03:32.228
Do you care who you steal from?

45
00:03:32.306 --> 00:03:36.403
My friend here has but a ha'penny.
What you take from him might be all he has.

46
00:03:36.478 --> 00:03:39.412
- Yeah. it is all I have.
- Heartbreaking. Do we care?

47
00:03:41.049 --> 00:03:44.849
- We don't care.
- We're dead men. Think about it... outlaws.

48
00:03:44.920 --> 00:03:46.547
Oh. that is sophisticated.

49
00:03:47.423 --> 00:03:49.789
Oh. big words. Scary.

50
00:04:08.379 --> 00:04:09.812
Those were horrible men.

51
00:04:09.880 --> 00:04:13.577
They could have left us here to die
for all they care.

52
00:04:13.651 --> 00:04:17.714
If they had not taken our weapons. I'd say we
should go after them and give them a hiding.

53
00:04:17.790 --> 00:04:19.621
A hiding to remember.

54
00:04:21.527 --> 00:04:23.119
But...

55
00:04:24.195 --> 00:04:25.595
you.

56
00:04:27.501 --> 00:04:29.627
You let me think...

57
00:04:32.406 --> 00:04:36.775
- You freed yourself. why did you not fight?
- Erm...

58
00:04:36.843 --> 00:04:38.368
I thought it best to wait.

59
00:04:38.446 --> 00:04:40.414
Why?

60
00:04:40.481 --> 00:04:45.818
Because. Much. you were right.
We should teach them a lesson.

61
00:04:45.888 --> 00:04:46.854
Gentlemen!

62
00:04:49.090 --> 00:04:50.523
Oh. no!

63
00:04:51.593 --> 00:04:53.424
Master. surely...

64
00:04:55.597 --> 00:04:58.588
Yeah. Let's go.

65
00:04:58.667 --> 00:05:00.066
Tick-tock.

66
00:05:01.136 --> 00:05:02.729
Tick-tock.

67
00:05:10.647 --> 00:05:13.013
Have I told you that I can't taste wine?

68
00:05:13.083 --> 00:05:15.574
Have the best. of course...

69
00:05:15.653 --> 00:05:17.712
but I don't have the palate for it.

70
00:05:31.136 --> 00:05:33.400
Yeah? What about a hat?

71
00:05:33.472 --> 00:05:35.167
Oh. yeah. yeah.

72
00:05:38.177 --> 00:05:40.805
I think your find that's not properly cooked.

73
00:05:53.927 --> 00:05:55.895
This is our forest too.

74
00:05:55.963 --> 00:05:57.726
I think you'll find.

75
00:06:02.737 --> 00:06:04.398
Take your clothes off.

76
00:06:10.479 --> 00:06:11.945
Robin!

77
00:06:13.515 --> 00:06:16.451
Aaagh! Aaaaghh!

78
00:06:19.288 --> 00:06:20.915
This is unacceptable.

79
00:06:21.891 --> 00:06:23.325
The master will...

80
00:06:23.393 --> 00:06:25.088
When this dispute is resolved.

81
00:06:25.163 --> 00:06:26.822
Robin will return. he will.

82
00:06:26.896 --> 00:06:29.127
Robin. he'll never be master of anywhere now.

83
00:06:29.199 --> 00:06:30.632
Master of Sherwood. maybe.

84
00:06:30.700 --> 00:06:33.135
- Robin of the wood.
- I like that. Robin of the wood.

85
00:06:33.204 --> 00:06:35.467
Robin Wood?

86
00:06:37.241 --> 00:06:39.209
- Guy would like that.
- You should tell him.

87
00:06:39.277 --> 00:06:41.802
- You tell him.
- I'm not gonna tell him. He might not like it.

88
00:06:42.513 --> 00:06:45.380
You are revolting. You know that?

89
00:06:46.485 --> 00:06:49.818
My master and I fought for five years
in the Holy Land.

90
00:06:49.888 --> 00:06:51.857
For what?

91
00:06:52.925 --> 00:06:54.984
So that people like you could run amok

92
00:06:56.061 --> 00:07:01.659
with your lawlessness
and your disgusting camp and your snide...

93
00:07:02.703 --> 00:07:04.694
your snide...

94
00:07:04.772 --> 00:07:07.570
Your snide. your snide...?

95
00:07:08.609 --> 00:07:10.008
- Dance.
- You. what?

96
00:07:10.978 --> 00:07:13.139
- Dance.
- No way.

97
00:07:14.648 --> 00:07:15.774
Ow!

98
00:07:16.884 --> 00:07:18.443
Dance!

99
00:07:25.895 --> 00:07:29.331
Very good. like dancing bears.

100
00:07:29.398 --> 00:07:31.025
How does it feel?

101
00:07:32.101 --> 00:07:34.569
You treat your fellow man like an animal!

102
00:07:36.005 --> 00:07:37.438
How does it feel?

103
00:07:37.507 --> 00:07:40.534
You take from those worse off than yourselves
and leave them to die.

104
00:07:40.611 --> 00:07:42.476
All right. you've made your point.

105
00:07:42.546 --> 00:07:45.242
You're not Englishmen.

106
00:07:45.315 --> 00:07:47.613
You're not the England we fought for.

107
00:07:47.684 --> 00:07:50.245
Men who think it is a boast to be dead.

108
00:07:50.854 --> 00:07:52.755
What do you think you're doing robbing him.

109
00:07:52.823 --> 00:07:56.123
when the Sheriff over there
is robbing it all 20 times over?

110
00:07:58.396 --> 00:08:02.128
Skulking in the woods.
while he steals spirits and livelihoods.

111
00:08:02.201 --> 00:08:06.001
Why are you skulking in the woods?
What are you gonna do about it?

112
00:08:07.973 --> 00:08:10.066
Stop him.

113
00:08:11.677 --> 00:08:13.508
I'm going to stop him.

114
00:08:13.579 --> 00:08:17.276
Well. you can't stop a sheriff.

115
00:08:18.152 --> 00:08:20.881
Only the Crown can withdraw his license.

116
00:08:20.954 --> 00:08:23.753
When the King returns.
he will have his comeuppance.

117
00:08:23.824 --> 00:08:26.883
Until then. we will scupper
his sadistic punishments.

118
00:08:26.960 --> 00:08:30.794
We will stop his insane taxes and give them
back to the poor where they belong.

119
00:08:30.864 --> 00:08:33.333
- Sure.
- We will rob him.

120
00:08:34.736 --> 00:08:37.296
And if you dead men had had
spines in your backs...

121
00:08:37.372 --> 00:08:39.863
that's what you'd have been doing
for the last five years.

122
00:08:39.942 --> 00:08:41.603
Rousing. lavender boy.

123
00:08:41.677 --> 00:08:43.974
- Good luck.
- Yeah. see ya.

124
00:08:44.847 --> 00:08:47.440
That'd be a mistake. I think you'll find.

125
00:09:00.431 --> 00:09:04.197
You are in no position to argue...

126
00:09:04.268 --> 00:09:06.259
dunderhead!

127
00:09:13.778 --> 00:09:15.335
Oh!

128
00:09:17.916 --> 00:09:21.080
Look. you've tied us up. we've tied you up.

129
00:09:21.153 --> 00:09:25.021
We could call it quits.
We could all be on our way.

130
00:09:26.359 --> 00:09:27.327
Him...

131
00:09:27.394 --> 00:09:29.054
- I do not like.
- It is mutual.

132
00:09:33.233 --> 00:09:35.701
Are you Robin of Locksley?

133
00:09:35.769 --> 00:09:38.363
Robin. Earl of Huntingdon.

134
00:09:40.340 --> 00:09:41.831
Good.

135
00:09:44.512 --> 00:09:45.876
Another hour.

136
00:09:47.181 --> 00:09:48.910
This is not necessary. Where is Robin?

137
00:09:50.752 --> 00:09:51.719
Talk!

138
00:09:53.622 --> 00:09:55.988
He will never be your master again.

139
00:09:56.891 --> 00:10:00.555
You need have no fear of reprisals from him.
I'm your master now.

140
00:10:00.629 --> 00:10:01.596
For good.

141
00:10:03.099 --> 00:10:05.590
At least have the courtesy to untie him.

142
00:10:08.972 --> 00:10:12.066
Locksley? You brought us home.

143
00:10:12.142 --> 00:10:15.600
- It seems there may be a reward.
- 20 pounds.

144
00:10:15.679 --> 00:10:18.205
Take him down. See if we can
get summat for this rabble too.

145
00:10:18.849 --> 00:10:21.751
- Me? I'm supposed to be dead.
- Me too. they won't recognize you.

146
00:10:21.820 --> 00:10:24.015
Well. if they do. I'll be hanged.

147
00:10:24.089 --> 00:10:26.250
- John?
- John can't go. can he?

148
00:10:26.324 --> 00:10:28.952
If they're gonna recognize anyone.
it's gonna be John.

149
00:10:29.027 --> 00:10:30.926
We all go.

150
00:10:31.763 --> 00:10:34.425
It is unfortunate.

151
00:10:34.499 --> 00:10:36.832
A man goes to war.

152
00:10:36.903 --> 00:10:40.532
his spirit can be damaged.
his vision blurred.

153
00:10:40.606 --> 00:10:43.131
his understanding of law and order.

154
00:10:43.209 --> 00:10:46.474
This is what has happened to Robin.

155
00:10:46.546 --> 00:10:50.506
I have heard that
there are camps in the Holy Land

156
00:10:51.785 --> 00:10:55.448
where men are taught to hate their own land.

157
00:10:55.523 --> 00:10:59.117
to return home to wreak
havoc and destruction.

158
00:10:59.193 --> 00:11:02.994
Maybe this is what has happened to Robin.
we don't know. But what we do know...

159
00:11:03.065 --> 00:11:07.592
is that by his actions in Nottingham.

160
00:11:07.669 --> 00:11:11.766
your former master. did not. as some of
the romantics amongst you might believe.

161
00:11:11.840 --> 00:11:13.832
strike a blow for freedom.

162
00:11:14.944 --> 00:11:16.537
Make no mistake about it.

163
00:11:16.613 --> 00:11:19.172
He perverted the course of justice.

164
00:11:19.248 --> 00:11:23.709
and in so doing.
he attacked the very fabric of our state.

165
00:11:25.088 --> 00:11:27.750
The state that we all work for.

166
00:11:27.824 --> 00:11:30.952
the state that we all pay our taxes for.

167
00:11:35.633 --> 00:11:37.658
He would rob us of that.

168
00:11:38.703 --> 00:11:40.695
Of our taxes. of our hard work.

169
00:11:52.786 --> 00:11:54.343
Another tongue. I suppose.

170
00:11:57.991 --> 00:12:02.451
No. no. no. no!

171
00:12:02.529 --> 00:12:05.362
- Oh. God! No!
- No!

172
00:12:05.431 --> 00:12:08.366
That is nasty... and that is brutish.

173
00:12:08.435 --> 00:12:09.902
- That is Alice.
- Alice?

174
00:12:09.970 --> 00:12:11.938
- My wife.
- You're Alice's John?

175
00:12:12.006 --> 00:12:13.166
She thought you were dead.

176
00:12:14.175 --> 00:12:16.075
It's you they want. we go now.

177
00:12:16.778 --> 00:12:18.677
You can't. you'll hang.

178
00:12:18.746 --> 00:12:21.214
There is no time. I can save your wife.

179
00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:23.046
Put me down.

180
00:12:25.253 --> 00:12:27.278
Untie me. My bow. quickly.

181
00:12:27.355 --> 00:12:29.950
I am good with a bow.

182
00:12:30.026 --> 00:12:32.085
- You saw him shoot your feet.
- Trust me.

183
00:12:46.844 --> 00:12:48.937
He's here.

184
00:12:49.413 --> 00:12:50.608
Find him.

185
00:12:50.682 --> 00:12:52.615
- Let's go.
- Godspeed.

186
00:12:53.284 --> 00:12:54.683
What?

187
00:12:54.752 --> 00:12:56.982
You have served me well. my friend.

188
00:12:57.055 --> 00:12:59.422
And I have led you to this.

189
00:12:59.491 --> 00:13:01.082
- Apologies.
- No.

190
00:13:01.159 --> 00:13:03.924
Go. I will find a way through this.

191
00:13:04.929 --> 00:13:06.864
- The Sheriff will hang you.
- If he does.

192
00:13:06.933 --> 00:13:08.958
at least I will not die a dead man.

193
00:13:14.406 --> 00:13:17.934
Good scheme. Sheriff. Very effective.

194
00:13:18.010 --> 00:13:20.173
Impressive logic.

195
00:13:20.248 --> 00:13:22.773
Now. I wonder.

196
00:13:23.783 --> 00:13:26.048
If I tell you where I am.

197
00:13:26.120 --> 00:13:28.554
can I claim the 20 pounds?

198
00:13:28.623 --> 00:13:31.592
That would be a pound or so
for each family here.

199
00:13:33.828 --> 00:13:35.660
Eat a whole winter off that.

200
00:13:35.731 --> 00:13:37.392
Amusing.

201
00:13:37.465 --> 00:13:39.434
Put down your weapon.
you're surrounded.

202
00:13:39.501 --> 00:13:41.628
I am Guy of Gisborne.

203
00:13:41.703 --> 00:13:44.365
the new lord of this manor
and soon to be Earl of Huntingdon.

204
00:13:45.375 --> 00:13:48.708
Your presence here is no longer required.
Put down your weapon.

205
00:14:19.277 --> 00:14:21.245
That was a cruel game to play.

206
00:14:23.416 --> 00:14:25.179
Game?

207
00:14:27.252 --> 00:14:28.845
You don't understand.

208
00:14:28.921 --> 00:14:32.220
You do not play games with me.

209
00:14:34.927 --> 00:14:36.986
You made a mistake in Nottingham.

210
00:14:37.064 --> 00:14:40.625
Hm? Trying to be the peasants' hero.

211
00:14:40.701 --> 00:14:43.671
Well. why don't you be the peasants' hero
and show me how it's done?

212
00:14:43.738 --> 00:14:48.300
Oh. shall we have a meeting
in the morning to discuss it?

213
00:14:48.377 --> 00:14:50.207
A clue - no.

214
00:14:51.713 --> 00:14:53.545
In the morning...

215
00:14:53.615 --> 00:14:54.741
you shall hang.

216
00:15:00.255 --> 00:15:01.415
Aww.

217
00:15:01.491 --> 00:15:03.287
All hope lost.

218
00:15:08.731 --> 00:15:11.200
- I liked him.
- I did not.

219
00:15:11.267 --> 00:15:13.360
He saved your wife.

220
00:15:14.537 --> 00:15:16.506
"Liked"?

221
00:15:16.574 --> 00:15:18.268
He's not dead.

222
00:15:53.013 --> 00:15:54.345
Fool.

223
00:15:59.320 --> 00:16:01.618
Ah... Are we rich?

224
00:16:02.824 --> 00:16:05.019
- What's the matter?
- Saw his wife.

225
00:16:05.794 --> 00:16:08.194
- No reward?
- My master gave himself in.

226
00:16:08.263 --> 00:16:10.994
- To the Sheriff?
- The Sheriff was cutting out tongues.

227
00:16:12.100 --> 00:16:14.832
He could hardly stand by
and watch people lose their tongues.

228
00:16:14.905 --> 00:16:17.896
That would be funny. wouldn't it?

229
00:16:17.973 --> 00:16:19.873
If instead of "Cat got your tongue?"

230
00:16:20.744 --> 00:16:22.506
They said. "Sheriff got your tongue?"

231
00:16:22.578 --> 00:16:24.068
What?

232
00:16:24.147 --> 00:16:28.709
If someone was a bit. you know. quiet.
you'd go. "What's the matter?

233
00:16:28.785 --> 00:16:30.811
"Sheriff got your tongue?"

234
00:16:34.025 --> 00:16:37.426
Look. we cannot just sit here.
We've got to do something.

235
00:16:37.495 --> 00:16:40.861
We've got to go to Nottingham
and we've got to... get him out.

236
00:16:40.931 --> 00:16:43.026
How?

237
00:16:43.101 --> 00:16:45.899
- No point anyway.
- No point?

238
00:16:45.970 --> 00:16:47.768
You would be dead if Robin had not...

239
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:49.865
- That's true.
- You would be dead.

240
00:16:49.942 --> 00:16:54.403
Mind you. I weren't supposed to hang in
the first place. That was just a confusion.

241
00:16:54.481 --> 00:16:57.109
Look. you can't just let him die. Will?

242
00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:06.124
Very well.

243
00:17:06.192 --> 00:17:07.558
I shall go alone.

244
00:17:07.628 --> 00:17:08.685
See ya.

245
00:17:08.761 --> 00:17:10.730
Oi! Hold it. no horse.

246
00:17:26.616 --> 00:17:28.584
In which house is my wife?

247
00:17:28.651 --> 00:17:29.845
I will fetch her.

248
00:17:29.919 --> 00:17:31.716
- Fetch her where?
- Here.

249
00:17:31.787 --> 00:17:33.550
A woman can live in the forest same as us.

250
00:17:33.624 --> 00:17:37.024
- Alice can't live in the forest.
- Why not?

251
00:17:37.093 --> 00:17:39.585
Ah... there 's something you don't know.

252
00:17:51.508 --> 00:17:53.840
Not so high and mighty now. are we?

253
00:17:55.813 --> 00:17:57.110
Oh!

254
00:17:57.182 --> 00:18:00.675
That's for the priest trick.
Could have cost me my job.

255
00:18:00.752 --> 00:18:02.448
One job to save four lives?

256
00:18:04.823 --> 00:18:07.657
Won't be saving anyone now. my lovely.
wherever you're from.

257
00:18:07.727 --> 00:18:09.785
He's not Robin of Locksley any more.

258
00:18:09.862 --> 00:18:12.798
Robin Wood. they're calling him.

259
00:18:12.865 --> 00:18:13.924
Robin Hood?

260
00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:16.969
There will be no hood for you tomorrow.
my lovely.

261
00:18:17.037 --> 00:18:20.096
The Sheriff wants the rebels
to see the fear in your eyes.

262
00:18:20.172 --> 00:18:23.006
He wants them to see your eyes pop right out.

263
00:18:42.731 --> 00:18:44.858
- Nothing?!
- What can I do?

264
00:18:44.934 --> 00:18:47.402
I warned him. the Sheriff.

265
00:18:47.470 --> 00:18:49.199
Yes. my Lord. but...

266
00:18:49.271 --> 00:18:52.070
He should have listened to my father.
now he is an outlaw.

267
00:18:52.141 --> 00:18:55.372
- I know. my Ladyship.
- And not a very impressive one.

268
00:18:55.445 --> 00:18:57.777
That is...

269
00:18:59.382 --> 00:19:00.816
Forgive me.

270
00:19:02.086 --> 00:19:06.080
That is not fair. he is most impressive.

271
00:19:06.157 --> 00:19:10.389
He is caught after just one day.
Does that impress you?

272
00:19:11.263 --> 00:19:14.357
He gave himself up to save tongues.

273
00:19:14.432 --> 00:19:17.196
- Tongues?
- In Locksley.

274
00:19:17.269 --> 00:19:22.070
The Sheriff was cutting out people's tongues
until somebody told him where Robin was.

275
00:19:23.075 --> 00:19:25.043
I hate the Sheriff...

276
00:19:27.613 --> 00:19:30.810
and I hate you.
if you aren't gonna help Robin.

277
00:19:31.817 --> 00:19:37.848
Young man. I will speak in court. of course.
but your master has doomed himself.

278
00:19:37.924 --> 00:19:40.256
His fate is...

279
00:19:40.327 --> 00:19:41.295
Resign yourself.

280
00:19:44.832 --> 00:19:47.596
In the Holy Land. my master had dreams.

281
00:19:49.604 --> 00:19:50.799
He spoke your name.

282
00:19:57.278 --> 00:19:58.746
Good night.

283
00:20:22.907 --> 00:20:24.637
Who are you?

284
00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:25.971
- Who are you?
- John.

285
00:20:26.043 --> 00:20:27.601
- John what?
- John Little.

286
00:20:27.678 --> 00:20:29.976
- Oh!
- But people call me Little John.

287
00:20:30.047 --> 00:20:32.074
- Do you know why?
- Why?

288
00:20:32.151 --> 00:20:35.051
Because my father was called John too.
John Little.

289
00:20:36.388 --> 00:20:39.825
He was a hero. He was big. I think.

290
00:20:39.892 --> 00:20:42.019
What's your name?

291
00:20:42.695 --> 00:20:44.162
I am...

292
00:20:45.566 --> 00:20:47.534
I'm a friend of your mother' s.

293
00:20:48.869 --> 00:20:52.531
- How is she?
- Always tired. always sewing.

294
00:20:52.607 --> 00:20:54.266
- But do you know what?
- What?

295
00:20:54.340 --> 00:20:58.711
Everything's gonna be better now
because Robin's back from the Holy Land.

296
00:20:58.780 --> 00:21:00.303
Oh?

297
00:21:00.381 --> 00:21:04.842
He always makes sure people have enough
to eat. I had a feast at the big house.

298
00:21:04.919 --> 00:21:07.752
and I had so much pork my belly ached.

299
00:21:08.524 --> 00:21:10.582
and Mother had fish. but...

300
00:21:10.658 --> 00:21:12.853
Eugh! Fish I do not like.

301
00:21:13.396 --> 00:21:15.489
F... Fish is her favorite.

302
00:21:16.097 --> 00:21:18.760
Robin will come back from Nottingham.

303
00:21:18.834 --> 00:21:20.631
- Won't he?
- I...

304
00:21:20.703 --> 00:21:22.466
Little John!

305
00:21:23.739 --> 00:21:25.332
Where are you? Little John?

306
00:21:25.409 --> 00:21:28.708
- Do you want to come in?
- I don't think I can. Little John.

307
00:21:29.313 --> 00:21:31.246
John!

308
00:21:31.314 --> 00:21:33.943
It's late. come on.

309
00:21:52.503 --> 00:21:54.233
I've realized something about you.

310
00:21:54.306 --> 00:21:55.774
I thought you didn't want to talk.

311
00:21:55.842 --> 00:21:58.970
- Mm. that was before I realized.
- Realized what?

312
00:21:59.045 --> 00:22:01.605
You are a renowned marksman with the bow.

313
00:22:01.681 --> 00:22:05.845
You saw me about to excise a tongue or two.
you could have shot me. why didn't you?

314
00:22:06.854 --> 00:22:10.119
You had men everywhere. I had only a few.

315
00:22:11.325 --> 00:22:15.456
- We were outnumbered.
- Yeah. well. that may be true.

316
00:22:15.529 --> 00:22:16.826
But...

317
00:22:18.265 --> 00:22:19.733
you gave yourself up.

318
00:22:19.801 --> 00:22:25.569
I care about those people. my people.
more than I care about myself.

319
00:22:25.640 --> 00:22:29.201
- You would not understand.
- Yeah. but that's not the point.

320
00:22:29.277 --> 00:22:31.507
- Do you want to know what the point is?
- No.

321
00:22:31.580 --> 00:22:35.711
The point is you care more about my life
than you do about your own.

322
00:22:38.522 --> 00:22:41.958
- No.
- Then why didn't you kill me?

323
00:22:42.025 --> 00:22:44.618
Surely you must have known
that I would see you executed.

324
00:22:46.430 --> 00:22:48.261
Have you lost your nerve?

325
00:22:49.100 --> 00:22:52.091
Have you lost your taste for blood? Hm?

326
00:22:52.169 --> 00:22:56.129
Robin of Locksley. honored for his service
in the King's private guard.

327
00:22:56.207 --> 00:22:58.870
How many men did you kill
in the Holy Land. I wonder.

328
00:22:58.944 --> 00:23:01.037
Yet here we are in Locksley.

329
00:23:01.113 --> 00:23:03.707
people that you love very much in trouble.

330
00:23:03.782 --> 00:23:06.343
and you have the chance to shoot me
but you don't take it.

331
00:23:07.219 --> 00:23:10.416
I would kill you in an instant.

332
00:23:11.490 --> 00:23:13.584
Well. maybe.

333
00:23:13.660 --> 00:23:16.355
If that was the only way
to prevent bloodshed. but...

334
00:23:18.964 --> 00:23:20.762
But it wasn't the only way. was it?

335
00:23:21.936 --> 00:23:27.340
No. you didn't have to kill me
because you could sacrifice yourself...

336
00:23:29.277 --> 00:23:31.370
and that is what you did.

337
00:23:32.948 --> 00:23:34.915
You think of me what you will.

338
00:23:35.984 --> 00:23:38.452
If I am dying tomorrow...

339
00:23:38.520 --> 00:23:40.147
it makes no difference.

340
00:23:40.822 --> 00:23:43.621
Oh. look who doesn't want to talk now.

341
00:23:45.929 --> 00:23:48.123
Jailer. open the gate.

342
00:23:53.404 --> 00:23:55.530
You're free to go.

343
00:23:55.605 --> 00:23:57.073
But I should say if you do.

344
00:23:57.141 --> 00:23:59.973
then tomorrow one or two
of your villager friends...

345
00:24:00.043 --> 00:24:03.172
Well. they won't be. how shall we say.
on speaking terms with you.

346
00:24:12.624 --> 00:24:15.184
I like it. this is good.

347
00:24:18.330 --> 00:24:23.860
I do not know why Englishmen
travel 2.000 miles to fight evil...

348
00:24:23.936 --> 00:24:26.166
when the real cancer is right here.

349
00:24:27.974 --> 00:24:30.443
Listen. I can hear a noise.
can you hear a noise?

350
00:24:31.611 --> 00:24:34.547
I think it's a dead man talking.

351
00:24:48.963 --> 00:24:50.430
I'd have gone if I were you.

352
00:24:50.498 --> 00:24:52.591
You're not me.

353
00:24:53.836 --> 00:24:59.139
# Have you ever kissed
a boy called John?

354
00:24:59.209 --> 00:25:05.636
# For if you've never kissed
a boy called John

355
00:25:05.714 --> 00:25:09.047
# You don't know what you've missed

356
00:25:09.118 --> 00:25:13.852
# Not kissing Little John #

357
00:25:36.749 --> 00:25:39.047
Think the whiney one'll make it?

358
00:25:40.319 --> 00:25:42.947
What's he gonna do?
Stroll into Nottingham and say.

359
00:25:43.021 --> 00:25:45.923
"Excuse me. can my friend
lavender boy go free?"

360
00:25:45.992 --> 00:25:48.358
Lambs to the slaughter. both of 'em.

361
00:25:49.463 --> 00:25:53.922
- Could have given him the horse.
- Then we lose a horse. too. Think about it.

362
00:25:54.001 --> 00:25:56.491
If Robin dies. the people of Locksley
will be like you.

363
00:25:56.570 --> 00:25:58.037
What do you mean "like us"?

364
00:25:58.105 --> 00:26:00.836
They'll have nothing left to live for.
They'll be dead men.

365
00:26:00.909 --> 00:26:03.503
Well. you go and save him. then. See ya!

366
00:26:03.578 --> 00:26:07.412
We don't do town. We're outlaws.
We're on the run.

367
00:26:07.482 --> 00:26:09.211
What happens to loved ones you leave?

368
00:26:09.284 --> 00:26:11.752
- Town is death.
- Have you seen what happens to a family

369
00:26:11.821 --> 00:26:14.812
- when there is only one breadwinner?
- Heartbreaking!

370
00:26:14.889 --> 00:26:18.122
Are you deaf?! We don't go to Nottingham!

371
00:26:18.194 --> 00:26:20.356
We go to Nottingham!

372
00:26:26.002 --> 00:26:30.268
To what do we owe the pleasure
of your company. Sir Guy?

373
00:26:36.414 --> 00:26:41.978
I would be pleased if you would come
and visit me at Locksley. now that it's mine.

374
00:26:42.054 --> 00:26:44.488
I do not know.

375
00:26:44.556 --> 00:26:48.014
I have ambitions which are greater.
of course. you know that.

376
00:26:49.429 --> 00:26:53.126
But for now to have land once more
in the Gisborne name.

377
00:26:53.199 --> 00:26:54.563
my father would be proud.

378
00:26:54.633 --> 00:26:56.967
I am very glad for you.

379
00:26:57.036 --> 00:27:00.665
Some of my men. I know this for a fact.
used to laugh at my title.

380
00:27:01.874 --> 00:27:04.605
Guy of Gisborne...
when there was no Gisborne.

381
00:27:04.677 --> 00:27:06.612
And Locksley is your Gisborne?

382
00:27:07.748 --> 00:27:09.772
Yes. actually...

383
00:27:11.185 --> 00:27:12.914
I am intent on changing its name.

384
00:27:12.987 --> 00:27:15.251
Does changing a name
really make a difference?

385
00:27:15.322 --> 00:27:20.089
When a woman marries. she changes her name.
It makes a difference.

386
00:27:20.161 --> 00:27:22.686
- And what of Robin?
- What of Robin?

387
00:27:22.763 --> 00:27:25.825
He will contest your acquisition
of his lands. surely.

388
00:27:25.902 --> 00:27:28.665
- He will die.
- If he is found guilty.

389
00:27:28.737 --> 00:27:31.229
There 's no need for a trial.
He will hang in the morning.

390
00:27:31.307 --> 00:27:33.571
There must be a trial. It is the law.

391
00:27:33.643 --> 00:27:36.545
Yeah. but he is an outlaw.

392
00:27:38.014 --> 00:27:42.247
You see. in these straitened times.
the Sheriff has made special provision.

393
00:27:42.319 --> 00:27:45.651
Outlaws are classed as enemies of war.
thus we can hold them without trial.

394
00:27:45.722 --> 00:27:47.816
- No.
- And we can execute them without trial.

395
00:27:47.892 --> 00:27:49.152
No. it cannot be.

396
00:27:49.225 --> 00:27:51.660
- We're at war.
- Yes. in the Holy Land.

397
00:27:51.728 --> 00:27:54.424
That does not mean
we dispense with justice here.

398
00:27:54.499 --> 00:27:56.659
I'm sorry. I was not expecting you.

399
00:27:56.733 --> 00:27:59.532
Do not worry. Father.
Sir Guy was just leaving.

400
00:28:54.764 --> 00:28:57.096
Shoo! Shoo!

401
00:28:58.035 --> 00:28:59.524
Go away. shoo!

402
00:29:00.638 --> 00:29:02.732
Please!

403
00:29:11.715 --> 00:29:13.650
Who's a good boy. eh?

404
00:29:17.322 --> 00:29:19.290
Need some help?

405
00:29:26.532 --> 00:29:28.227
Yeah. I was. er...

406
00:29:28.301 --> 00:29:30.792
I was just checking up there

407
00:29:30.871 --> 00:29:35.103
and. yes. as I thought.
the ladder is completely useless.

408
00:29:37.210 --> 00:29:39.974
Well. come on. then.

409
00:29:59.535 --> 00:30:01.730
Come on then. my lovely.

410
00:30:01.804 --> 00:30:03.568
Let's have some entertainment.

411
00:30:07.943 --> 00:30:09.934
- Where is it?
- Where is what?

412
00:30:10.012 --> 00:30:14.576
Please. the ring my father gave you years ago
before he knew the wickedness of your heart.

413
00:30:14.652 --> 00:30:19.055
Madam. I told you before.
asking doesn't usually work.

414
00:30:19.123 --> 00:30:20.715
I'll do his thumb.

415
00:30:20.791 --> 00:30:24.659
- Will those work?
- These? They're lovely.

416
00:30:25.229 --> 00:30:27.858
- When he speaks will you hear?
- Of course.

417
00:30:27.933 --> 00:30:31.164
Well. that I cannot allow.
You might get there first and steal the ring.

418
00:30:31.236 --> 00:30:33.932
Madam. I can assure you.
I'm a man of simple pleasures.

419
00:30:35.041 --> 00:30:37.669
Inflicting pain. that's enough for me.

420
00:30:37.744 --> 00:30:40.076
Maybe. but if the ring is not
where he tells me.

421
00:30:40.146 --> 00:30:42.706
suspicion will fall on you
and that would be unfair.

422
00:30:42.782 --> 00:30:45.615
- I will speak with him alone first. You may go.
- I can't do that.

423
00:30:45.685 --> 00:30:48.519
Wait outside. he cannot escape.
He will not dare attack me.

424
00:30:48.589 --> 00:30:50.557
- No. I...
- Leave.

425
00:30:51.592 --> 00:30:53.253
Yes. Your Ladyship.

426
00:30:59.100 --> 00:31:00.795
You are an utter fool.

427
00:31:00.868 --> 00:31:02.860
- You said that already.
- Oh. you listened?

428
00:31:02.937 --> 00:31:05.804
I also told you confronting
the Sheriff wouldn't work.

429
00:31:05.874 --> 00:31:08.398
- You didn't listen to that.
- I did not have much choice.

430
00:31:08.476 --> 00:31:11.241
Everything is a choice.
everything we do. Grow up.

431
00:31:11.313 --> 00:31:15.272
I prevented unjust hangings.
I protected people from my village.

432
00:31:15.351 --> 00:31:18.514
- Oh. that will make your death romantic.
- It would make it honorable.

433
00:31:18.587 --> 00:31:22.649
Honorable? And what about the people
you were so honorably protecting?

434
00:31:22.725 --> 00:31:25.058
Who will protect them when you're dead?

435
00:31:25.127 --> 00:31:27.858
Oh! What is it with men and glory?

436
00:31:27.931 --> 00:31:29.593
Glory above sense and above reason.

437
00:31:29.667 --> 00:31:32.158
- It is principle.
- Principle is making a difference

438
00:31:32.236 --> 00:31:34.066
and you can't do that if you're dead.

439
00:31:34.137 --> 00:31:37.574
You could have stayed here instead
of following your king to the Holy Land

440
00:31:37.642 --> 00:31:41.840
if you'd cared so much about
your precious people. but you didn't.

441
00:31:42.581 --> 00:31:44.673
You chose war.

442
00:31:44.749 --> 00:31:46.684
You chose glory.

443
00:31:52.357 --> 00:31:53.381
What is this about?

444
00:31:55.829 --> 00:31:58.992
It is about you saying that...

445
00:31:59.065 --> 00:32:02.193
you care about the people of Locksley.
when...

446
00:32:02.268 --> 00:32:05.362
the truth is you ran off to battle
thousands of miles away.

447
00:32:13.180 --> 00:32:14.943
You had something on your cheek.

448
00:32:20.689 --> 00:32:22.520
Right. this is what we do.

449
00:32:22.591 --> 00:32:26.083
Stand by the door. I'll scream.
in he comes. you strike him and run.

450
00:32:26.161 --> 00:32:29.859
I've paid a man by the east gate. you'll not
be seen if you leave before the day watch.

451
00:32:29.932 --> 00:32:31.832
- I cannot go unseen.
- You cannot go seen.

452
00:32:31.900 --> 00:32:34.870
- I cannot let the Sheriff win.
- Have you not heard a word I've said?

453
00:32:34.938 --> 00:32:37.269
Trust me. I have a plan.

454
00:32:37.340 --> 00:32:39.570
Well. half a plan.

455
00:32:42.211 --> 00:32:43.804
I love it when you look at me in anger.

456
00:32:43.881 --> 00:32:45.075
Oh!

457
00:32:54.726 --> 00:32:56.193
This is a rescue.

458
00:32:59.864 --> 00:33:01.662
And we are undetected.

459
00:33:02.734 --> 00:33:05.363
In the dungeon! Outlaw!
Open this door.

460
00:33:05.437 --> 00:33:06.905
Ah!

461
00:33:08.140 --> 00:33:10.074
Oh. thank God!

462
00:33:10.142 --> 00:33:13.044
This man needs help.

463
00:33:16.416 --> 00:33:19.282
- Thank you for coming.
- Quick. before they see the open gates.

464
00:33:19.351 --> 00:33:22.652
Hang on. Hold an escape route for me.
I need five minutes.

465
00:33:22.723 --> 00:33:25.418
There 's something I must do
before I can go with you.

466
00:33:25.492 --> 00:33:28.758
- What?
- If I am longer than that. leave without me.

467
00:33:29.998 --> 00:33:31.965
- Yes.
- Thank you.

468
00:33:33.168 --> 00:33:37.036
Master. no.
You cannot go back in there.

469
00:33:37.105 --> 00:33:40.735
If you go back in and die.
then I will die. of grief.

470
00:33:41.643 --> 00:33:43.838
So you must come now. if only to save me.

471
00:33:43.912 --> 00:33:46.541
That is why I love you.

472
00:33:48.585 --> 00:33:50.882
And you... I need help.

473
00:33:50.954 --> 00:33:53.718
- It is dangerous.
- Yes.

474
00:33:59.063 --> 00:34:02.555
Why him when you love me?
Why not me?

475
00:34:06.536 --> 00:34:08.562
Here they come!

476
00:34:30.062 --> 00:34:32.189
Whoa. wait. Last man.

477
00:35:08.437 --> 00:35:12.967
Hello there! I was just passing
and the Sheriff said for me to drop in...

478
00:35:14.411 --> 00:35:15.379
at any time.

479
00:35:19.582 --> 00:35:22.017
My Lord. Robin has escaped!

480
00:35:38.538 --> 00:35:39.505
What do you want?

481
00:35:39.572 --> 00:35:43.564
Yesterday in Locksley.
you revealed your true colors.

482
00:35:43.643 --> 00:35:44.769
Today. I reveal mine.

483
00:35:46.346 --> 00:35:47.711
You were right.

484
00:35:47.780 --> 00:35:50.044
I have lost my taste for bloodshed

485
00:35:50.116 --> 00:35:53.245
but if you ever callously or needlessly

486
00:35:53.319 --> 00:35:55.584
hurt anyone as a way of getting to me.

487
00:35:55.656 --> 00:35:59.217
if you cut out a tongue or brand an arm.

488
00:35:59.293 --> 00:36:03.229
or even so much as pluck the hair
of an innocent person to get to me.

489
00:36:03.298 --> 00:36:07.166
in the name of King Richard.
so help me. I will kill you.

490
00:36:10.739 --> 00:36:12.867
- I don't believe you.
- Trust me.

491
00:36:12.942 --> 00:36:15.376
What has changed since yesterday?
Nothing.

492
00:36:18.814 --> 00:36:20.144
Prove it.

493
00:36:20.216 --> 00:36:23.845
I will not change. I will stoop low. so...

494
00:36:24.621 --> 00:36:26.054
kill me now.

495
00:36:35.932 --> 00:36:38.423
Impressive.

496
00:36:38.502 --> 00:36:41.836
But each arrow that hits the wood...
Well. that is a point lost. isn't it?

497
00:36:42.306 --> 00:36:44.536
What's surprising is
you haven't even maimed me.

498
00:36:44.610 --> 00:36:47.807
I'm not even grazed.
surely I deserve at least that.

499
00:36:51.784 --> 00:36:53.877
Are you afraid of authority?

500
00:36:53.951 --> 00:36:56.319
Or is it. secretly...

501
00:36:56.388 --> 00:36:58.584
you know that I'm right?

502
00:36:58.658 --> 00:37:01.559
That we must have law and order.

503
00:37:01.628 --> 00:37:03.460
I think it is.

504
00:37:03.531 --> 00:37:08.332
I think that is why I shall
have you hang yourself.

505
00:37:12.305 --> 00:37:13.671
Now I have maimed you.

506
00:37:14.542 --> 00:37:16.568
It's a scratch. hm?

507
00:37:16.645 --> 00:37:18.613
My point. well. it still stands.

508
00:37:19.247 --> 00:37:21.306
- Lavender?
- Lavender.

509
00:37:24.086 --> 00:37:28.181
But my pain shall be salved
by a much sweeter balm.

510
00:37:28.256 --> 00:37:30.248
the knowledge that you are weak.

511
00:37:30.325 --> 00:37:34.626
As weak as your charming.
sweet conscience is strong.

512
00:37:38.601 --> 00:37:40.125
You overestimate my conscience.

513
00:37:42.806 --> 00:37:47.607
Now. do precisely as I say.
We're going to the tower.

514
00:37:49.980 --> 00:37:50.969
Stop!

515
00:37:51.482 --> 00:37:52.950
Stop!

516
00:37:53.851 --> 00:37:56.184
Do not harm those men. they're free to go.

517
00:37:56.254 --> 00:37:58.223
I have an announcement to make.

518
00:37:58.289 --> 00:37:59.756
- I.
- I...

519
00:37:59.824 --> 00:38:01.348
Vaizey. Sheriff of Nottingham...

520
00:38:01.426 --> 00:38:04.554
- In recognition.
...in recognition...

521
00:38:04.629 --> 00:38:06.893
- Of my.
...of my...

522
00:38:06.965 --> 00:38:10.299
illegal actions yesterday in Locksley...

523
00:38:10.369 --> 00:38:13.635
- Do humbly apologize.
...do humbly apologize...

524
00:38:13.707 --> 00:38:19.236
to the innocent people
who have suffered at my hands.

525
00:38:19.312 --> 00:38:22.282
I promise to pay 500 pounds.

526
00:38:22.350 --> 00:38:25.113
I promise to pay...

527
00:38:26.721 --> 00:38:29.690
No! No. I cannot go on.

528
00:38:29.758 --> 00:38:31.588
You will have to kill...

529
00:38:31.660 --> 00:38:34.185
Guards! Guards!

530
00:38:34.263 --> 00:38:35.491
Stop those men!

531
00:39:00.591 --> 00:39:02.286
Much! Much!

532
00:39:03.360 --> 00:39:05.054
And shoot Locksley!

533
00:39:16.541 --> 00:39:18.304
Much!

534
00:39:20.912 --> 00:39:23.176
Tie this off.

535
00:39:31.390 --> 00:39:33.051
Robin. where?

536
00:39:33.125 --> 00:39:34.286
Here!

537
00:39:41.768 --> 00:39:43.793
- You. defend me.
- Me?

538
00:39:44.438 --> 00:39:45.770
Yes!

539
00:39:51.312 --> 00:39:52.438
Yes!

540
00:40:15.605 --> 00:40:18.039
- That arrow hurt. lavender boy!
- Heartbreaking.

541
00:40:24.281 --> 00:40:25.680
Ready?

542
00:40:26.718 --> 00:40:28.185
Go!

543
00:41:14.336 --> 00:41:15.769
That her?

544
00:41:15.838 --> 00:41:17.806
She's your wife?

545
00:41:18.707 --> 00:41:20.938
What does she see in you?

546
00:41:21.010 --> 00:41:23.206
Look. she's seen it. Look!

547
00:41:33.457 --> 00:41:36.450
- That is good.
- Yeah.

548
00:42:00.620 --> 00:42:02.054
Come on!

549
00:42:23.044 --> 00:42:26.707
You know. I myself.
have no family at all. of course.

550
00:42:26.782 --> 00:42:28.273
No family.

551
00:42:28.850 --> 00:42:31.979
No wife. children.

552
00:42:32.054 --> 00:42:35.649
Strangely. it doesn't bother me.
Not at all.

553
00:42:36.759 --> 00:42:38.227
Not at all.

554
00:42:44.967 --> 00:42:47.596
Excuse me. I think you'll find
that's not properly cooked.

555
00:42:57.315 --> 00:42:59.283
Very funny.

556
00:43:00.305 --> 00:44:00.319
